WEBVTT

00:00.968 --> 00:04.236
♪♪

00:04.338 --> 00:07.573
Ahem! Where
ya goin?

00:07.775 --> 00:12.544
Since you three were unable to
retrieve my Bewitching Bell,

00:12.646 --> 00:15.848
we need another source
of great magical power

00:15.950 --> 00:18.517
to defeat Twilight
and her friends.

00:21.055 --> 00:24.356
<i> ♪ [plodding music] ♪</i>

00:24.458 --> 00:26.191
He's gone!

00:27.028 --> 00:28.327
I don't trust him.

00:28.629 --> 00:29.746
None of us do.

00:29.847 --> 00:32.364
Which is why double-crossing
him with his own bell

00:32.466 --> 00:34.633
will be so satisfying.

00:34.735 --> 00:37.402
<i>If</i> we can figure
out how to use it.

00:37.504 --> 00:38.570
Hmmm.

00:40.441 --> 00:43.108
Twilight Sparkle
may be the worst....

00:43.210 --> 00:44.977
But she does know stuff.

00:45.079 --> 00:46.745
She once said the
archives in Canterlot

00:46.847 --> 00:48.747
has a restricted area.

00:48.949 --> 00:52.017
Celestia and Luna love
to hoard information

00:52.119 --> 00:55.955
for themselves. If there's
an answer, it's there.

00:56.157 --> 00:58.891
My triumphant
return to Canterlot?

00:59.093 --> 01:01.360
I like the sound of that...

01:01.462 --> 01:03.462
Oh my gosh! Road trip!

01:42.303 --> 01:46.238
♪♪

01:46.340 --> 01:48.840
Sorry to interrupt. We
know you're busy planning

01:48.942 --> 01:53.012
The Summer Sun Celebration
as we requested. But..

01:53.114 --> 01:55.881
Oh! Things seem...
calmer

01:55.983 --> 01:57.617
than we would
have expected.

01:57.919 --> 01:59.118
No complaints here.

01:59.220 --> 02:01.253
With the exception of
the odd trivia night,

02:01.355 --> 02:02.621
I've made a lot
of progress

02:02.723 --> 02:04.857
since the Royal
Swanifying Ceremony.

02:05.159 --> 02:08.594
You may not know this about me,
but I occasionally freak out!

02:09.530 --> 02:11.563
That was a joke. I
wanted to show you

02:11.665 --> 02:13.132
with the Summer
Sun Celebration

02:13.234 --> 02:17.036
how much I've improved.
So I focused on delegating

02:17.138 --> 02:19.405
and trusting others!
It's been GREAT!

02:19.707 --> 02:22.842
That's.. actually what we
came to talk to you about.

02:22.944 --> 02:25.211
This may be the last
Summer Sun Celebration

02:25.313 --> 02:26.979
you'll need to plan.

02:27.481 --> 02:28.781
Did I do something wrong?

02:28.883 --> 02:31.450
Of course not. It's just
that the Celebration

02:31.552 --> 02:34.553
has always been about
us. My defeat of Luna...

02:34.655 --> 02:36.956
And, thanks to you
and your friends,

02:37.058 --> 02:38.891
my reunion with
my sister.

02:38.993 --> 02:40.960
Now that we're leaving,
we don't see a need

02:41.062 --> 02:42.594
for the holiday any longer.

02:42.696 --> 02:43.647
Now that you're...?

02:43.748 --> 02:47.099
My sister and I have decided
the time for us to retire

02:47.201 --> 02:49.702
is upon us. You and
your friends have proven

02:49.804 --> 02:51.771
you are ready to
lead Equestria.

02:52.473 --> 02:55.507
So let this be the last
Summer Sun Celebration

02:55.609 --> 02:59.812
as Equestria leaves behind
the old to embrace the new.

03:04.518 --> 03:08.054
My goodness! How are YOU
feeling about all this?

03:08.256 --> 03:10.089
Something like this could
definitely send you

03:10.191 --> 03:11.991
into full
freaky-outy mode.

03:12.193 --> 03:15.761
I'm actually fine. But if
this is going to be the last

03:15.863 --> 03:18.197
Summer Sun Celebration,
I want to make sure

03:18.299 --> 03:20.466
it's the best
Celebration <i>ever</i>.

03:20.968 --> 03:21.834
Please don't give
us more work...

03:21.936 --> 03:23.636
Please don't give
us more work.....

03:23.938 --> 03:25.437
So even though
everything was done,

03:25.539 --> 03:27.073
I thought of a few
last-minute changes

03:27.175 --> 03:28.407
I could use
your help with.

03:28.609 --> 03:30.309
Gah! I knew it!

03:30.411 --> 03:33.279
Discord: Oh! The end
of a beloved holiday?

03:33.381 --> 03:35.647
Last-minute changes
to a celebration?

03:35.849 --> 03:37.716
That sounds positively...

03:37.818 --> 03:39.051
Chaotic!

03:39.153 --> 03:40.786
What are YOU doing here?

03:40.888 --> 03:44.156
I've known Celestia and Luna
longer than any of you!

03:44.258 --> 03:47.493
I terrorized them; they
turned me into stone...

03:49.530 --> 03:51.831
If this is the last
Summer Sun Situation,

03:51.933 --> 03:53.733
I simply can't miss it.

03:54.035 --> 03:56.769
Well, I see I've arrived
just in time for the

03:56.971 --> 03:59.171
"Twilight gives her
friends an impossibly long

03:59.273 --> 04:02.208
and overly detailed
list" predicament!

04:02.410 --> 04:04.977
I guess some-draconequis
isn't the know-it-all

04:05.079 --> 04:06.212
he thinks he is!

04:06.414 --> 04:10.149
♪♪

04:10.251 --> 04:11.517
<i>This</i> is it?

04:11.619 --> 04:12.284
What?

04:12.486 --> 04:14.854
We were kinda with
Discord on this one...

04:14.956 --> 04:17.823
No more crazy lists.
No more freaking out.

04:17.925 --> 04:20.159
With your help, I
know we've got this.

04:20.261 --> 04:23.795
Oh! Character
growth is so boring.

04:23.897 --> 04:26.131
Do I at least get
my own note card?

04:29.003 --> 04:32.304
There. Now, I need to
go rewrite my speech,

04:32.406 --> 04:34.140
but if you all look at
your cards, you'll see-

04:34.242 --> 04:37.376
Can't talk now! Have so much
to get done before sunrise!

04:44.351 --> 04:47.787
Why are so many ponies up
in the middle of the night?

04:47.889 --> 04:49.989
It's that silly sun holiday.

04:50.091 --> 04:53.926
How many holidays do you
ponies HAVE? No matter.

04:54.028 --> 04:56.428
Getting into the castle
won't be a problem.

04:56.630 --> 04:59.131
Are you sure
about that?

04:59.933 --> 05:01.934
<i> ♪ [sting] ♪</i>

05:05.706 --> 05:09.074
Oh. Those are
new. But even so...

05:11.512 --> 05:14.814
<i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

05:18.319 --> 05:20.653
Transfer. Have to
head inside. Open up.

05:20.855 --> 05:23.388
<i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

05:23.490 --> 05:25.724
<i> ♪ [chimes] ♪</i>

05:25.826 --> 05:28.360
<i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

05:29.730 --> 05:31.064
Right. Of course. Heh.

05:34.101 --> 05:36.302
Uh, do yours get glitchy, too?

05:37.204 --> 05:39.605
More medallions, more
problems. Am I right?

05:41.876 --> 05:44.043
They've increased
security into the castle.

05:44.145 --> 05:46.946
This is going to be more
challenging than I thought.

05:48.983 --> 05:52.284
Could you NOT go popping us
all over the place please?

05:52.386 --> 05:55.688
Time is of the
essence! Let's.. go team!

05:56.490 --> 05:59.458
We need to know what we're
doing before we go and do it.

05:59.860 --> 06:01.493
Pinkie, you and I
are givin' Braeburn

06:01.595 --> 06:03.963
and the Appleoosan ponies
some adjustments to the menu.

06:04.065 --> 06:06.332
Fluttershy and I are meeting
the pegasi from Cloudsdale

06:06.434 --> 06:07.933
to give them changes
to the weather.

06:08.235 --> 06:11.203
Spike, we're going to update
The Flaming Sky Firework

06:11.305 --> 06:13.639
unicorn troupe with
Twilight's new vision.

06:13.741 --> 06:15.374
And I'm supposed to...

06:15.576 --> 06:19.912
Make sure Discord doesn't
do anything.. <i>Discord-y</i>!?

06:20.014 --> 06:22.281
Well, that's
annoyingly specific...

06:26.120 --> 06:30.522
Increased security on a
crowded holiday with Twilight

06:30.624 --> 06:35.094
and their friends bumbling
around? This is impossible!

06:35.196 --> 06:39.665
Oh, no. This is perfect!
We need a distraction

06:39.767 --> 06:42.835
and those ridiculous
ponies just gave it to us!

06:42.937 --> 06:45.871
Now, do exactly
as I tell you...

06:48.809 --> 06:52.911
♪♪

06:53.013 --> 06:56.381
Step away from the wagons!
Official food tasters here

06:56.483 --> 06:58.317
on official
food-tasting business!

07:01.189 --> 07:03.822
Huh. It ain't gonna be easy,

07:03.924 --> 07:05.724
but I think we can whip
up these new cookies

07:05.826 --> 07:07.593
Twilight wants
before sunrise.

07:07.895 --> 07:10.729
If anypony can handle some
last-minute bakin', Braeburn,

07:10.831 --> 07:11.764
it's y'all.

07:13.134 --> 07:14.933
We brought plenty
for the celebration,

07:15.235 --> 07:18.170
but if she keeps testin',
we might be in trouble.

07:21.442 --> 07:24.376
But I see a
suspicious-looking COOKIE!!

07:29.116 --> 07:31.149
<i> ♪ [scary music] ♪</i>

07:32.920 --> 07:33.820
You OK?

07:34.722 --> 07:37.656
I feel... weak
all of a sudden.

07:39.359 --> 07:41.526
♪♪

07:41.628 --> 07:43.194
Is somepony back there?

07:43.296 --> 07:47.165
♪♪

07:49.703 --> 07:50.535
What is it!?

07:50.637 --> 07:53.672
Everypony! Get
away from the food

07:53.874 --> 07:56.975
till we figure out
what's goin' on!

08:07.321 --> 08:09.621
The princess
wants WHAT!?

08:10.023 --> 08:12.858
Just what's on that
little card. No big deal.

08:12.960 --> 08:17.562
No big dea..!? It's a much more
aggressive weather pattern

08:17.664 --> 08:19.164
then what was
originally ordered!

08:19.266 --> 08:22.434
This is very irregular!
We'll need to-

08:22.636 --> 08:26.538
No! First we must...
Wait! We, Oh..!

08:26.640 --> 08:27.872
Take a breath!

08:29.076 --> 08:30.742
Let it out slowly.

08:31.845 --> 08:34.145
Tell the princess
we will do our best.

08:34.247 --> 08:37.116
We're sure you're
doing an excellent job.

08:37.318 --> 08:39.050
Oh! Yeah. Totally.

08:39.152 --> 08:42.053
You're not gonna panic
and screw it up <i>at all</i>.

08:43.957 --> 08:46.758
I-I-I'm not built for
high pressure situations!

08:46.860 --> 08:49.828
Golly. Sounds like
you need some help.

08:50.330 --> 08:51.197
Who are you?

08:51.398 --> 08:53.465
Somepony who's organized
enough to handle

08:53.567 --> 08:57.035
the small stuff so you can
focus on the BIG picture!

08:57.237 --> 09:00.306
The big...? YES!
That sounds right!

09:01.108 --> 09:04.976
Ha, ha. This kind of weather
has to be handled delicately.

09:05.078 --> 09:09.214
Good thing I'm here. I'll
take care of <i>everything</i>.

09:10.484 --> 09:11.283
<i> ♪ [fanfare] ♪</i>

09:14.755 --> 09:15.787
Whoa!

09:15.889 --> 09:19.291
The Flaming Sky Firework
Troupe is a marvel.

09:19.393 --> 09:21.627
We take pride in what we do.

09:22.029 --> 09:24.262
These last-minute changes
aren't too challenging,

09:24.364 --> 09:24.999
are they?

09:25.500 --> 09:30.235
Ha! The more challenging, the
better! We aim to <i>astound</i>.

09:30.337 --> 09:33.606
Now, if you don't mind, we DO
have a new routine to prepare.

09:34.508 --> 09:36.575
Horns at the ready!

09:36.877 --> 09:39.744
♪♪

09:43.784 --> 09:45.617
Very impressive!

09:45.719 --> 09:48.119
Thank you. Unfortunately,
we have no room

09:48.221 --> 09:52.524
for anypony else at
this time. Ahem. I'm sorry?

09:52.626 --> 09:54.059
Crackle Cossette.

09:54.161 --> 09:56.561
And I don't want to join
your silly little troupe.

09:56.763 --> 09:58.397
Pardon me?

09:58.699 --> 10:03.001
Oh! I meant no offense! It
just seems a pity for unicorns

10:03.103 --> 10:07.672
to waste their talents on
something so... inconsequential.

10:09.643 --> 10:11.910
Unicorns wield <i>magic</i>.

10:12.112 --> 10:15.581
We are the most POWERFUL
ponies in the land.

10:15.883 --> 10:18.951
Don't you ever feel you're
destined for more than...

10:19.353 --> 10:21.352
...<i>performances</i>?

10:24.591 --> 10:26.257
It's all coming together!

10:26.359 --> 10:28.126
I really think this is
going to be the best

10:28.228 --> 10:30.429
Summer Sun
Celebration EVER!

10:30.831 --> 10:33.064
You've done an
outstanding job!

10:33.166 --> 10:35.433
We've ALL done an
outstanding job!

10:35.535 --> 10:36.568
And what about me?

10:36.770 --> 10:39.204
You'll be happy to know that
I have been watching myself

10:39.306 --> 10:43.308
all night and I have yet
to do ONE Discord-y thing!

10:43.410 --> 10:46.077
Luna: Now that truly
<i>is</i> amazing.

10:46.179 --> 10:49.948
Twilight, we know you
had, uh, difficulties

10:50.050 --> 10:52.584
using the amulet to
raise the sun and moon.

10:52.786 --> 10:54.719
We thought perhaps
a practice session

10:54.821 --> 10:57.155
before the festivities
might be in order?

10:57.557 --> 11:02.894
That's... a good idea.
Thank you all. So much.

11:02.996 --> 11:05.930
♪♪

11:06.032 --> 11:07.866
I sure am
proud'a her.

11:08.068 --> 11:09.968
Yeah! She
finally realizes

11:10.070 --> 11:11.270
things will turn
out fine,

11:11.472 --> 11:13.071
even when she isn't
micromanaging

11:13.173 --> 11:14.105
every little detail.

11:14.875 --> 11:16.875
Braeburn?! What's wrong!?

11:17.177 --> 11:24.349
Earth ponies. Sick. Food
missin'. Can't.... bake... anything...

11:24.585 --> 11:25.884
Something's wrong
with the weather!

11:25.986 --> 11:29.054
Storms, hurricanes,
fog! You name it.

11:29.156 --> 11:30.822
It's a disaster
out there!

11:30.924 --> 11:32.958
Rarity! Please
inform Her Highness

11:33.060 --> 11:34.893
that we will not
be performing.

11:35.195 --> 11:37.228
A simple fireworks
show is beneath us!

11:37.330 --> 11:38.764
We're BETTER than that.

11:39.066 --> 11:42.100
What the...? Everything
was fine a minute ago.

11:42.502 --> 11:45.004
Apparently, a lot can
change in a minute.

11:45.806 --> 11:50.842
♪♪

11:50.944 --> 11:53.445
It's total chaos
out there!

11:54.147 --> 11:55.480
Don't look
at me!

11:55.682 --> 11:57.048
What are we gonna do!?

11:57.150 --> 11:58.083
Twilight: Do about what?

11:59.887 --> 12:02.955
Ah! What are YOU doing here!?

12:03.557 --> 12:05.590
I forgot these.
You guys OK?

12:05.892 --> 12:07.826
Twilight, we're
sorry but-

12:07.928 --> 12:09.894
But! Er. We don't
know what to do,

12:09.996 --> 12:11.996
now that everything's
all ready!

12:12.098 --> 12:13.498
Ha ha ha!

12:13.900 --> 12:16.167
I guess I was
TOO organized!

12:16.269 --> 12:18.370
I'll try to come up with
a few last-minute errands

12:18.472 --> 12:20.171
for you before
sunrise.

12:20.273 --> 12:22.674
Well, that's a relief!

12:23.076 --> 12:26.011
Explain to me why we
didn't tell her the truth?

12:26.213 --> 12:28.446
Twilight is finally learning
not to let her stress

12:28.548 --> 12:29.948
get the better of her!

12:30.050 --> 12:31.583
If she finds out
everything went wrong,

12:31.685 --> 12:33.251
it could be
devastating!

12:33.353 --> 12:35.186
She would be
so upset!

12:35.288 --> 12:37.122
She'll totally
freak out!

12:37.524 --> 12:39.491
Well, what do
y'all suggest?

12:39.493 --> 12:42.594
Oo-oo-ooh! Let's just fix it
all before she notices!

12:42.696 --> 12:43.895
No lying necessary!

12:43.997 --> 12:45.130
I guess...

12:45.432 --> 12:46.565
We'd need a miracle.

12:46.767 --> 12:49.668
We HAVE a miracle!
Don't we?

12:51.071 --> 12:54.239
I suppose I COULD
fix everything...

12:54.641 --> 12:56.875
But isn't the
real miracle here

12:56.977 --> 13:00.812
the miracle of teamwork
and character growth?

13:02.249 --> 13:04.516
Oh, come on!

13:04.918 --> 13:07.752
Discord is right.
Twilight needs US.

13:07.854 --> 13:09.988
Whatever happened,
we can fix this.

13:11.424 --> 13:12.891
What DID happen?

13:17.564 --> 13:20.598
Best. Road trip. EVER!

13:25.072 --> 13:30.675
♪♪

13:31.845 --> 13:33.378
Even if I was an
actual doctor,

13:33.480 --> 13:35.179
I would have no
idea what's wrong.

13:35.281 --> 13:36.615
There's gotta
be a reason.

13:37.017 --> 13:38.517
Something got
'em all sick.

13:39.019 --> 13:40.185
Maybe the food?

13:40.387 --> 13:44.990
I ate the food too! Does
that mean I'm sick? Oh, no!

13:48.061 --> 13:49.360
Nope. I feel fine.

13:52.162 --> 13:59.034
<i> ♪ [mysterious music] ♪</i>

14:01.408 --> 14:02.907
♪♪

14:03.777 --> 14:10.749
♪♪

14:10.873 --> 14:13.673
<i> ♪ [heroic music] ♪</i>

14:13.753 --> 14:15.219
I don't know how
this happened!

14:15.321 --> 14:17.789
I'm going to be
FIRED for sure!

14:17.891 --> 14:19.557
Rainbow Dash and
the Wonderbolts

14:19.659 --> 14:22.694
will have ALL the weather
rounded up any minute.

14:22.796 --> 14:25.231
AHHHH! [thud]

14:25.355 --> 14:26.355
Or not!

14:29.569 --> 14:30.352
Not here.

14:30.653 --> 14:32.536
The Archives are in a
different part of the castle.

14:37.644 --> 14:39.911
What about aiming
for perfection?

14:40.013 --> 14:41.880
We've set our
sights higher.

14:42.082 --> 14:43.448
Higher than perfection?

14:43.550 --> 14:45.950
<i>Higher</i> than putting
on a silly little show

14:46.052 --> 14:47.318
for the other ponies.

14:47.920 --> 14:51.489
But you were so excited
before! What changed!?

15:01.333 --> 15:06.905
♪♪

15:07.007 --> 15:08.873
You two just enjoy
the festivities!

15:08.975 --> 15:11.176
I have a few surprises
in store for-

15:11.778 --> 15:12.877
Yes, Discord?

15:12.979 --> 15:16.214
Oh! Well, don't mind me. I'm
just here for the chaos.

15:17.283 --> 15:19.684
Oh-oh-oh. And here we go!

15:21.054 --> 15:22.654
What is Rainbow Dash doing?

15:24.791 --> 15:26.591
Pinkie? Is
this soup?

15:26.693 --> 15:29.961
Yes! I... was
really hungry?

15:30.063 --> 15:32.864
Nopony understands
wanting to take pride

15:32.966 --> 15:35.233
in your work
more than I do!

15:35.435 --> 15:36.734
You could do more
with your magic

15:36.836 --> 15:38.803
than make frilly
dresses!

15:39.005 --> 15:41.739
Pfft! Nopony makes
frills anymore!

15:41.841 --> 15:44.075
This season is actually
all about simplicity and-

15:44.177 --> 15:46.043
Not the point, Rarity!

15:47.313 --> 15:48.246
Princess!

15:48.848 --> 15:52.450
I BEG your forgiveness.
It's entirely MY fault!

15:52.752 --> 15:53.518
What is?

15:55.421 --> 15:56.221
That!

15:56.623 --> 16:00.291
Oh...um! Just a slight hiccup
in the weather! Ha, ha.

16:01.215 --> 16:04.415
♪♪

16:04.597 --> 16:06.497
Applejack? What
is going on?

16:06.599 --> 16:08.867
I TOLD y'all this
was a bad idea

16:08.969 --> 16:11.570
but nopony ever
LISTENS TO ME!

16:11.972 --> 16:13.304
That's IT!

16:17.120 --> 16:17.820
Ooof!

16:18.345 --> 16:21.179
I thought everything was
fine! What is going on!?

16:21.481 --> 16:23.582
Everything <i>was</i> going fine.

16:23.684 --> 16:25.417
Until it totally wasn't.

16:25.819 --> 16:27.886
We tried to fix
it ourselves...

16:27.988 --> 16:29.254
Why didn't
you tell me!?

16:29.556 --> 16:31.389
We didn't want
you to freak out.

16:31.491 --> 16:33.291
And you thought NOT
telling me everything

16:33.393 --> 16:35.994
was a total disaster
would avoid a freak-out!?

16:36.396 --> 16:39.964
When you say it like that, it
sounds like a really bad plan.

16:42.202 --> 16:44.102
Here it comes...

16:44.704 --> 16:48.539
I know how I used to react.
But I really have changed!

16:48.741 --> 16:50.875
Panicking won't
solve anything.

16:52.712 --> 16:55.379
But we can handle whatever
problems come our way,

16:55.481 --> 16:57.748
as long as we handle
them... together!

16:57.850 --> 17:00.251
Celestia: Spoken like a
true leader.

17:00.453 --> 17:01.586
How can we help?

17:01.988 --> 17:03.622
I love a good to-do list!

17:04.224 --> 17:05.656
So tell me exactly
what happened

17:05.758 --> 17:09.026
so we can figure out exactly
what to do to fix it!

17:09.128 --> 17:11.829
<i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

17:11.931 --> 17:16.167
♪♪

17:24.310 --> 17:52.915
♪♪

17:53.974 --> 18:06.045
♪♪

18:07.554 --> 18:20.325
♪♪

18:22.034 --> 18:23.534
♪♪

18:24.504 --> 18:29.073
♪♪

18:38.151 --> 18:49.823
<i> ♪ [royal fanfare] ♪</i>

18:52.932 --> 18:55.800
This celebration has
always been a reminder

18:55.902 --> 18:57.435
not to fear the night,

18:57.637 --> 19:00.338
for there is always a new
day to look forward to.

19:00.540 --> 19:03.007
But as we look towards
Equestria's future,

19:03.309 --> 19:05.609
I am sad to say that
today will be the last

19:05.711 --> 19:07.578
Summer Sun Celebration.

19:09.549 --> 19:11.816
...because there is something
even more important

19:11.918 --> 19:12.751
to celebrate.

19:13.553 --> 19:15.820
There are two ponies
who have watched over us

19:16.122 --> 19:18.689
night and day for as
long as we can remember.

19:18.891 --> 19:22.460
We will no longer commemorate
their battle or their reunion.

19:22.662 --> 19:25.263
Instead, we will take
this day to celebrate

19:25.365 --> 19:27.432
how much they mean
to all of us.

19:27.734 --> 19:30.268
From this day forward
today will be known as..

19:30.470 --> 19:33.003
The Festival of
the Two Sisters!

19:36.176 --> 19:38.142
We don't know
what to say...

19:38.244 --> 19:43.247
♪♪

19:43.349 --> 19:47.952
Hee hee! A brand-new holiday?
You're my kinda princess!

19:48.054 --> 19:49.654
I'm just glad we
pulled it off.

19:49.756 --> 19:53.557
About that... We just wanted
to say.. we're real sorry.

19:53.659 --> 19:55.493
You did tell us
you'd changed.

19:55.695 --> 19:58.696
As your friends, we
should have trusted you.

19:59.098 --> 20:01.298
Next time you say you're
not gonna freak out,

20:01.400 --> 20:02.351
we'll believe you.

20:02.452 --> 20:05.103
Good. Because I'm sure there's
going to plenty of things

20:05.205 --> 20:07.305
I'll need my best
friends' help with.

20:08.741 --> 20:09.540
Whee!

20:09.642 --> 20:10.708
Whoa!

20:11.796 --> 20:16.247
You know, it really does seem
like you just might be ready

20:16.349 --> 20:20.084
for whatever comes
next, Your Majesty.

20:22.722 --> 20:25.656
So...? Did you find what
you were looking for?

20:26.058 --> 20:30.928
Once again, I've found success
where you all find failure!

20:31.030 --> 20:32.763
I have located
what I sought

20:32.865 --> 20:35.900
and tomorrow I will set
out to retrieve it.

20:36.002 --> 20:36.902
When I return,

20:37.003 --> 20:40.903
Equestria will finally
be ours for the taking.

20:41.106 --> 20:41.773
Hmph!

20:42.275 --> 20:44.008
Oh, stop pouting.

20:44.110 --> 20:45.976
You knew you couldn't
stay that buff.

20:46.078 --> 20:48.679
You had to return all the life
force to those earth ponies

20:48.781 --> 20:50.715
so Grogar doesn't
suspect anything.

20:50.817 --> 20:53.117
I don't have to like it.

20:53.619 --> 20:55.119
Well, I don't like
that we worked so hard

20:55.221 --> 20:57.388
to destroy their party and
they still pulled it off,

20:57.490 --> 20:59.657
but you don't see
ME complaining!

21:00.159 --> 21:03.794
Our goal wasn't to destroy;
it was to distract.

21:04.964 --> 21:07.598
And now we have
exactly what we need.

21:07.700 --> 21:09.767
And no time to waste.

21:09.869 --> 21:13.337
We have to master the Bell
before Grogar returns.

21:13.439 --> 21:17.341
We've managed to stay one step
ahead of everypony so far...

21:17.543 --> 21:21.879
You know.. It really was
super-easy to get all those

21:21.981 --> 21:24.715
earth ponies and
pegasi and unicorns

21:24.817 --> 21:26.184
to turn on each other.

21:26.286 --> 21:31.922
It was, wasn't it. Now <i>that</i>
is something to think about...
